// Muxr default layout for sessions created by the mobile app
// (CreateSession with no client-supplied layout).
//
// The Muxr client renders tab/pane controls itself, so sessions it
// creates must NOT show zellij's tab-bar (top) or status-bar (bottom). Those
// bars are plugin panes that only appear when a layout declares them; the
// built-in `default` layout does. By defining an empty `default_tab_template`
// (just `children`, no bar plugins), EVERY tab — including ones the app creates
// at runtime via NewTab — opens with a single bare terminal pane and no bars.
//
// This file is bundled into the muxrd binary (include_str!) and written
// to <data_dir>/layouts/ at create time; its absolute path is passed as
// `zellij --layout <path> attach --create-background`. It is server-authored
// and trusted, so it
// is exempt from the client-layout name allowlist (see grpc/session_ops.rs).
layout {
    default_tab_template {
        children
    }
}
